In honour of Reginald Marr Brydone (
1873 – 1943
), a prolific author of bryozoan species from the English Chalk and collector of the type material of the new species.

United Kingdom , England , Hampshire , south of Alton, Froxfield, Kings Lane;
Sternotaxis plana Zone
, late Turonian.

cavity located in the distal part of the maternal zooid and below the colony surface (
Fig. 5H
). Avicularia interzooidal, elongate, longer than autozooids. Rostrum channelled, with elevated wing-like walls and pointed tip, spade-shaped, symmetrical or asymmetrical, dextral or sinistral. Proximal part rounded, shorter and wider than rostrum. Cryptocyst pustulose, concave, peripheral caverns rare. Opesia large, usually oval, rarely roundish, with thickened articular ridges bearing two very short teeth proximally and a long, slit-like opesiular indentation between teeth; opesiules lacking. Kenozooids rounded or oval, located usually at edges of colony (
Fig. 5B
). Cryptocyst finely pustulose with proximal peripheral caverns. Opesia roundish, small. Closure plates, intramural reparative budding of zooids not observed.
